ou can stream audio to your Home Mini from any Bluetooth-enabled device. Here\u2019s how:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Open the Google Home app on your phone.<\/li>\n<li>Select your Home Mini &gt; Tap Settings.<\/li>\n<li>Navigate to \u201cAudio\u201d &gt; \u201cPaired Bluetooth Devices.\u201d<\/li>\n<li>Enable pairing mode and connect your phone or PC.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>After pairing, you can use your Home Mini like a regular speaker without needing Wi-Fi.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0What Functions Are Lost Without Wi-Fi?<\/h2>\n<p>When not connected to the internet, the Home Mini loses access to Google Assistant, smart home integrations, and voice recognition. Essentially, it becomes a basic Bluetooth speaker with no AI-driven features.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Is It Worth Using This Way?<\/h2>\n<p>While not its intended purpose, using the Mini offline is helpful for playing music or audio in situations where Wi-Fi is unavailable, such as while traveling or during network outages. However, for full smart features, a stable internet connection is always recommended.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Official Sources and Technical Insights<\/h2>\n<p>Google doesn\u2019t advertise offline use heavily, but the feature exists and is usable with prior setup. You can learn more about the product family on <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Google_Home\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia\u2019s Google Home page<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Conclusion<\/h2>\n<p>Yes, you can use your Google Home Mini as a speaker without Wi-Fi, provided it\u2019s already been configured and paired via Bluetooth. While you won\u2019t have smart features, it still works great for basic audio playback on the go.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Can I Use Google Home Mini as a Speaker Without Wi-Fi? The Google Home Mini is primarily a smart speaker that thrives with an internet connection, but you may be wondering: Can I use it as a regular speaker without Wi-Fi? The answer is ye